  "text": "In this paper, we study the connection to ensembling, and provide a comprehensive study complementary to the closely-related study in [CITATION_1] . There are substantial differences between [CITATION_2] and our work: (i) We show the architecture resemblance of the deeply-fused net and an ensemble of neural networks by expanding the deeply-fused net to a structure different from [CITATION_3] . (ii) We show the classification performance resemblance and the performance variation resemblance by changing the ensemble size and the ensemble component capability. We directly train the composed networks and ensembles from scratch for comparing their performances, instead of removing single layers/modules, or reordering modules at test time done in [CITATION_4] . (iii) Our study on how the training of the deep component networks is influenced by the shallow networks is also different from [CITATION_5] . In particular, we suggest that the deepest (plain) network introduce many layers to generate a large ensemble. (iv) Finally, guided by our analysis, we present a novel deeplyfused network with merge-and-run fusion.",
